docs.abstract: Warner Bros., HBO and Turner Broadcasting must ensure that diverse actors and crew members are “considered” for jobs. Progress will be reported annually.
docs.snippet: Warner Bros., HBO and Turner Broadcasting must ensure that diverse actors and crew members are “considered” for jobs. Progress will be reported annually.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Acknowledging a need to do “much more” to promote diversity, Warner Bros. and its corporate siblings, HBO and Turner Broadcasting, introduced a policy on Wednesday aimed at increasing the number of women and people of color involved in its movies and television shows.

headline.main: WarnerMedia Unveils Diversity Protocols for Movies and TV Shows
headline.print_headline: WarnerMedia Unveils A New Diversity Policy For Actors and Crew

docs.abstract: A report from the Council of Economic Advisers sought to counter Democrats’ criticism of slow wage growth when unemployment is low
docs.snippet: A report from the Council of Economic Advisers sought to counter Democrats’ criticism of slow wage growth when unemployment is low
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A mystery of the current economic recovery is why wages are stuck in neutral while economic growth revs faster. On Wednesday, the Trump administration tried to solve the puzzle by producing its own measure that shows wages are, in fact, growing.

headline.main: White House Says Wages Are Growing When Measured Differently
headline.print_headline: White House Crafts Yardstick to Show Wage Growth
